The `ClassCastException` is a runtime exception that can occur when you try to cast an object to a type that is not compatible with its actual type. It extends the `RuntimeException` class, which means that it is an unchecked exception and does not need to be handled by a `catch` block (although it can be caught and handled if desired). 

