Catching the `ClassCastException` certainly provides a simpler alternative to checking the `instanceof` the parent and handling the case where it is not a `LinearLayout`. It allows you to write more concise code, since you only need to cast the parent to `LinearLayout` and handle the resulting exception if it occurs.

