To add a text view of the latest data from a node of a Firebase Realtime Database, you need to do the following:

1. Set up Firebase in your Android project.

2. Add the dependency for Firebase Realtime Database in your app-level build.gradle file:

```groovy
implementation 'com.google.firebase:firebase-database:20.0.0'
```

3. Add an Internet permission to your AndroidManifest.xml:

```xml
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
```

4. Add the text view to your layout where you want to display the latest data, for example in your activity_main.xml file:

```xml
<TextView
    android:id="@+id/textViewData"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:text="Latest Data" />
```

5. In your MainActivity.java or Kotlin class, create a reference to your Firebase Realtime Database:

```java
FirebaseDatabase database = FirebaseDatabase.getInstance();
DatabaseReference myRef = database.getReference("your-node-name");
```

6. Create a ValueEventListener to get the data from the database and set it as the text in the text view:

```java
myRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(@NonNull DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        // Get the latest data
        String latestData = dataSnapshot.getValue(String.class);

        // Display it in the text view
        TextView textViewData = findViewById(R.id.textViewData);
        textViewData.setText(latestData);
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(@NonNull DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle any errors
        Log.w("Error", "Failed to read value.", databaseError.toException());
    }
});
```

Now, when the latest data in your specified node of your Firebase Realtime Database changes, it will automatically update the text view in your Android app.

